{
  "answer": "**The matla (opening couplet) of the first ghazal in *Diwan-E-Zauq* (Chapter 1: *Aankh us pur-jafa se ladti hai*) is:**\n\n**Transliteration:**  \nAankh us pur-jafa se ladti hai  \nJaan kashti qaza se ladti hai[^1]\n\n**Translation:**  \nMy eye against her cruel and faithless way contends,  \nMy soul against the ship of final fate contends.[^2]\n\nThis couplet introduces the ghazal's radif (\"ladti hai\") and rhyme scheme, a recurring theme of contention in love, fate, and existence throughout the poem.[^3]\n\n[^1]: Sheikh Ibrahim Zauq, *Diwan-E-Zauq*, [paragraph](/works/sheikh-ibrahim-zauq-diwan-e-zauq-0fa798/01-aankh-us-pur-jafa-se-ladti-hai/transliteration/#p-06b3b4).\n\n[^2]: Sheikh Ibrahim Zauq, *Diwan-E-Zauq*, [paragraph](/works/sheikh-ibrahim-zauq-diwan-e-zauq-0fa798/01-aankh-us-pur-jafa-se-ladti-hai/translation/#p-c3221c).\n\n[^3]: Sheikh Ibrahim Zauq, *Diwan-E-Zauq*, Chapter 1, [/works/sheikh-ibrahim-zauq-diwan-e-zauq-0fa798/01-aankh-us-pur-jafa-se-ladti-hai/translation/](works/sheikh-ibrahim-zauq-diwan-e-zauq-0fa798/01-aankh-us-pur-jafa-se-ladti-hai/translation/).",
